long_description: meant to bridge the gap between traditional outpatient therapy and hospital-based programming, vital living's adolescent & young adult intensive anxiety clinics offer an intermediate level of care. the iac is a private pay , structured 20-week program focused on anxiety management that teaches how to apply the basic skills necessary to lead a fuller, more enjoyable life. the adolescent iac is available to middle and high school students and the young adult iac is available to those over 18 years of age. weekly group (1.5 hours) comprised of accountability, process & education/skills. therapy offers support in taking control of the one thing that is within one's control; response to discomfort. learning how to interact differently with one's mind helps to create the space needed to exert more purposeful control over behavior in line with one's values. as a continuing education sponsor, vital living offers presentations on a variety of topics for professional development and/or continuing education credit.
